## � COMPUTER-AWARE EXECUTION MODEL

This project lives on two machines. How you delegate depends on where you are.

```bash
scutil --get ComputerName  # Check which machine you're on
```

| Computer | How to delegate grunt work |
|----------|--------------------------|
| **MacBook Pro** | Spin up sub-agents directly (Haiku, Flash, GPT-mini, etc.) |
| **Mac Mini** | Use Agent Hub → routes to local Ollama models |

**MacBook Pro:** You're talking to a top-level model (Claude, Gemini). Ask it to spawn a cheaper sub-agent for grunt work. No local models available.

**Mac Mini:** Agent Hub is available in `_tools/agent-hub/`. It routes tasks to local Ollama models (DeepSeek-R1, Qwen, etc.) autonomously. Prefer this for anything repetitive or CPU-heavy.

